<center><font size=7><b>Spy Hunter</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 8</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>Your superdooper spy car can shoot everything apart from the blue death-cars and the choppers. So, to blow up a helicopter, you'll have to pick up a missile from one of the trucks.
 <i>(Scott Donaldson in Your Spectrum issue 19)</i> 

<br><hr>
After the truck dumps you at the beginning of the game, be quick and drive back in before the ramp is raised. That way you'll have a rest from the traffic - no vehicles appear! If it's invincibility you're after, keep your finger on the up&nbsp;key while you're holed up in there.
 <i>(Scott Donaldson in Your Spectrum issue 19)</i> 

<br><hr>
There's just no point in going at top whack - trundling along in low gear is a much more effective way of zapping the other road hogs. And above all make sure you take out the red mean machines with the nasty Boedicea style knives on their&nbsp;wheels - or you could be cut up about it when they run you off the road.
 <i>(Scott Donaldson in Your Spectrum issue 19)</i> 

<br><hr>
When you're on the water, watch out for the blue boats. They drop mines, so the best bet is to drive slowly with your finger on the fire button. Keep to the right as far as possible when you're overtaking the yellow peril boats. That way you'll find it easier to dodge the missiles they fire at you and rejoin the road.
 <i>(Scott Donaldson in Your Spectrum issue 19)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Game bugs</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>If you follow the truck from the start, being careful not to run it off the road or shoot it, then no enemy agents' cars will appear on the screen.
 <i>(Andrew Billimore in Sinclair User issue 43)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Cheat modes</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>In Spy Hunter, when the helicopter comes along, go up behind and stop level with it. The copter fires bombs which blow up just before they reach you. While that is happening your score slowly ticks on.
 <i>(Andrew Graham in Sinclair User issue 42)</i> 

<br><hr>
In Spy Hunter, when the helicopter comes along, go up behind and stop level with it. The copter fires bombs which blow up just before they reach you. While that is happening your score slowly ticks on.
 <i>(Andrew Graham in Sinclair User issue 42)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Multiface pokes</i></b></font></td></tr>
